headline: Constellation Energy Earnings Beat Expectations. The Stock Is Dropping.
summary: Constellation Energy  stock fell in premarket trading Thursday despite posting second-quarter earnings and revenue came in above analyst expectations.  Constellation reported adjusted operating earnings of $1.91 per share, beating the $1.84 a share analysts had anticipated, according to FactSet.  Operating revenue of $6.1 billion handily topped the $4.9 billion Wall Street had forecast.
